# Security Tools Available on This System

## 🌐 Web Application Testing

### Vulnerability Scanners
- **Nikto** - Web server scanner for vulnerabilities
  ```bash
  nikto -h https://target.com
  ```

- **WPScan** ✓ - WordPress vulnerability scanner (already used)
  ```bash
  wpscan --url https://site.com --enumerate ap,u
  ```

- **SQLMap** - Automated SQL injection tool
  ```bash
  sqlmap -u "http://site.com/page.php?id=1" --batch --dump
  ```

### Directory/File Discovery
- **Dirb** - Directory brute forcer
  ```bash
  dirb https://target.com /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt
  ```

- **Gobuster** - Fast directory/file/DNS brute forcer
  ```bash
  gobuster dir -u https://target.com -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt
  ```

- **ffuf** - Fast web fuzzer
  ```bash
  ffuf -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -u https://target.com/FUZZ
  ```

- **wfuzz** - Web application fuzzer
  ```bash
  wfuzz -c -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt https://target.com/FUZZ
  ```

### Web Proxies & Interceptors
- **Burp Suite** - Web application security testing platform
  ```bash
  burpsuite
  ```

- **OWASP ZAP** - Zed Attack Proxy
  ```bash
  zaproxy
  ```

- **mitmproxy** - Interactive HTTPS proxy
  ```bash
  mitmproxy -p 8080
  ```

## 🔐 Password Cracking & Brute Force

### Hash Cracking
- **John the Ripper** ✓ - Password cracker (already used)
  ```bash
  john --wordlist=rockyou.txt hash.txt
  ```

- **Hashcat** ✓ - Advanced GPU password recovery (already used)
  ```bash
  hashcat -m 0 -a 0 hash.txt rockyou.txt
  ```

- **ophcrack** - Windows password cracker using rainbow tables
  ```bash
  ophcrack
  ```

### Online Brute Force
- **Hydra** ✓ - Network login cracker (tried)
  ```bash
  hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt site.com http-post-form "/login:user=^USER^&pass=^PASS^:F=error"
  ```

- **Medusa** - Parallel password cracker
  ```bash
  medusa -h target.com -u admin -P passwords.txt -M http
  ```

- **Patator** - Multi-purpose brute forcer
  ```bash
  patator http_fuzz url=http://site.com/login method=POST body='user=FILE0&pass=FILE1' 0=users.txt 1=passwords.txt
  ```

### Wordlist Generation
- **CeWL** - Custom wordlist generator from websites
  ```bash
  cewl https://target.com -w wordlist.txt -d 3
  ```

- **Crunch** - Wordlist generator
  ```bash
  crunch 8 8 -t @@@@2025 -o passwords.txt
  ```

